 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong and�@Member of the Central Military Commission of the WPK and First Vice�@Department Director of the WPK Central Committee Ri Yong Chol.�@ He learned about the unit' s performance of duty before walking the�@compound of the barracks reminiscent of a park to acquaint himself with its�@management. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing the barracks surrounded by persimmon trees heavily laden with red�@persimmons, outdoor resting places and entertainment and amusement places,�@he was greatly satisfied to learn that the unit splendidly spruced up the�@compound of the barracks and it planted a variety of many fruit trees, in�@particular. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the service and living of soldiers, going round an�@educational room, a bedroom, a mess hall, a kitchen, a washroom, a daily�@provision store and entertainment and logistic facilities,�@ No details of soldiers' life escaped him ranging from their watching TV,�@their use of publications, the temperature in their bedrooms to the amount�@of water in bathrooms and the preparation of food to their taste. He�@specified ways to improve them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He familiarized himself with the sideline job of the unit, looking round�@the barns crowded with fat ducks, geese, pigs and goats and the fish farm�@teeming with various species of fishes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Greatly pleased to learn that the unit has scrupulously organized the�@stockbreeding and the sideline job to provide its soldiers with good�@conditions for diet, he said that the KPA is a true pace-setter in�@self-reliance as it creates something from nothing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the feats performed by the officers and men of the unit,�@saying that they have set an example in the management of the unit as�@befitting the soldiers in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
